				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: PoD Kiting<a name="5893"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 1 03 1:02 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Yeah, after that first death in PoD I figured it all out and really got the hang of it.  I discovered that the secret was my Singing Steel Boots.  A little lev song and I was able to pull all 10 or so flies from that peninsula without a problem.  Here's how:
<br />
1) Pop SSBoots, 49 Selos, put up invis song.
<br />
2) Go to the end of the peninsula and target the fly down the back side of the hill.
<br />
3) Go back a little ways so I'm out of the immediate proximity aggro of the other flies
<br />
4) Drop Chant of Poison on the fly targeted, then run back to the Rock.
<br />
5) Swarm Kite as normal.
<br />
So the key was using lev song to be able to position myself better and not have to worry about falling in the water or anything.  Pulling the farthest fly basically caused it to run through all of the aggro ranges of everything else on the peninsula and grab them for me.
<br />
Since then, I've levelled like a mofo there.  I could be higher level, but I hung around at 52 to get a few AAs and try for a Nagafen raid for my RDS.  Didn't happen and I got impatient.
<br />
Enough rambling, but all that to say it took a few dives, but I've since mastered PoD flies, and only died two other times since.  Once to my ISP cutting out randomly, and once due to some very odd pathing I've noticed about the flies that I've now compensated for.
<br />
Thanks to everyone for advice.
<br />
Rock on!
<br />
~Myrmion
<br />
54 guildless Minstrel of Xegony</span></td>
