				<td colspan="2"><span>Yep, due north of the zoneline, past the first swarm area is an indent near the zonewall with a big rock in the middle.  That is a second swarm point for the Vetri's that are on the northern most islands.  Careful of the Malarians, red to me at 56 they cast and are bad news for bards. The times I've aggro'd one, I immediately ran to zone.  Good news is there you can easily outrun the train such that it almost never trains anyone. 
<br />

<br />
Also there, watch out for wandering rats. About 75% are uncharmable so it makes for a long swarm when you have to chant down 2 uncharmables from near full health.  Overall I'd pick the first spot over this one due to the shear number of mobs you can kite and the lack of wanderers.
<br />

<br />
Two more things on the northern swarm point I'm discussing:
<br />
- Supposedly you can pull goos from farther inland, though careful to avoid aggroing any spiders (see Malarian comment above).
<br />
- It is fairly common for CoD key quest groups to be very near there along the shore camping other mobs.  The only time I saw that myself was when nearly the entire group was guildie or alliance, so I could get them to move down a bit and move completely out of the say when I pulled.  You could not pull around them if they were on the shoreline so if they are uncooperative, the place could be camped.
<br />

<br />
Sorry this is a bit disjointed, busy at work today.
<br />

